			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Copper-containing slag</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">含铜渣</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Fayalite</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Fayalite</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Wastes</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Other waste</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Copper slag is a by-product of copper extraction by smelting. It is composed mainly of Fayalite, a type of Fe silicate glass. It can be used as an abrasive, particularly for removing mill scale, rust, dirt, paint and other coatings from metal. It is lighter than other types of slags, making it easier to transport and handle during construction projects. Copper mining and processing methods can expose and/or concentrate NORM, transforming them into Technologically Enhanced Naturally Occurring Radioactive Materials (TENORM).</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">铜渣是通过熔炼提取铜的副产品。其主要成分是一种铁硅酸盐玻璃--辉绿岩。它可用作磨料，特别是用于去除金属上的轧机垢、铁锈、污垢、油漆和其他涂层。它比其他类型的炉渣更轻，因此在建筑项目中更容易运输和处理。铜矿开采和加工方法会暴露和/或浓缩天然放射性物质，将其转化为技术增强型天然放射性物质（TENORM）。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>SiO2 and FeO</sumFormula>
		</dataSetInformation>
